race.comment: LILLIAN (5) sat handy last start over 1800m and was too strong late, winning by 0.3L. Getting out in trip now looks ideal for her and she still has plenty of upside. Can put herself close to the speed once again for CJP and with further improvement expected, she makes the most appeal. KIMBERLEY ROSE (3) ran over the top to score over this course and distance, winning by 1.2L. Brad Parnham remains in the saddle and she remains in the same grade. Trending the right way and can go back-to-back. LATE ARRIVAL (4) was scratched last week due to a stable mishap, but that's only a minor issue. The inside draw should see him on the speed from a good draw again and he's sure to make his presence felt. AUDIO BOY (6) is another who looks to be knocking on the door of a maiden win. Nottle's claim and an inside draw are both ticks and he won't be far away again. SNAZZLER (1) is right back in grade here and is not to be discounted.
